        "content": "\n**`_normalize_ats`** (ATS character normalization) — pure and high-value:\n```python\nfrom agent import _normalize_ats\n\nclass TestNormalizeAts:\n    def test_em_dash_and_smart_quotes_replaced(self):\n        html = \"<p>It\\u2019s \\u201Cgreat\\u201D \\u2014 really</p>\"\n        out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n        assert \"\\u2019\" not in out and \"\\u201C\" not in out and \"\\u2014\" not in out\n        assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_style_or_script_blocks(self):\n        html = '<style>body{content:\"\\u2014\"}</style><p>\\u2014</p>'\n        out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n        assert \"\\u2014\" in out.split(\"</style>\")[0]  # untouched inside style\n        assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1  # only the <p> one counted\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_tag_attributes(self):\n        html = '<a title=\"\\u2014\">x</a>'\n        out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n        assert 'title=\"\\u2014\"' in out  # inside a tag -> untouched\n        assert \"em-dash\" not in counts\n\n    def test_zero_width_chars_stripped(self):\n        out, counts = _normalize_ats(\"a\\u200bb\")\n        assert out == \"ab\"\n```\n\n**`cmd_db_new` / `cmd_db_mark`** — integration-ish, use a real temp `Store`:\n```python\nclass TestDbNewMark:\n    def test_first_run_uses_since_days_window(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        # no marker set -> since = now - since_days\n        ...\n    def test_truncation_respects_group_boundaries(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        # two jobs sharing first_seen must not be split across the limit\n        ...\n    def test_db_mark_rejects_non_iso_watermark(self, capsys):\n        rc = cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-timestamp\"])\n        assert rc == 2\n    def test_db_mark_requires_watermark_or_now(self, capsys):\n        rc = cmd_db_mark([])\n        assert rc == 2\n```\n\n**`_chrome_bin`** — untested; environment-dependent, needs `monkeypatch` on `shutil.which` and `Path.exists`.\n\n**`cmd_pdf_render`** — needs a real/fake Chrome binary or a `subprocess.run` monkeypatch; test the \"no such input file\" and \"render produced non-PDF output\" failure paths without invoking real Chrome:\n```python\nclass TestPdfRenderErrors:\n    def test_missing_input_file_returns_2(self, capsys):\n        rc = cmd_pdf_render([\"/no/such/file.html\"])\n        assert rc == 2\n\n    def test_render_failure_when_output_not_pdf(self, tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n        src = tmp_path / \"in.html\"; src.write_text(\"<html></html>\")\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"agent.subprocess.run\",\n                             lambda *a, **k: type(\"R\", (), {\"stderr\": \"boom\", \"returncode\": 1})())\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"agent._chrome_bin\", lambda: \"/bin/true\")\n        rc = cmd_pdf_render([str(src)])\n        assert rc == 1\n```\n\n**`main()` argv routing** — untested (mode-word vs flag splitting, `-i`/`--interactive` handling):\n```python\nclass TestMainRouting:\n    def test_help_flag_short_circuits(self, capsys):\n        assert main.__wrapped__ if False else None  # invoke via sys.argv monkeypatch\n    def test_bare_invocation_is_interactive(self, monkeypatch):\n        ...\n    def test_flag_after_mode_words_splits_correctly(self, monkeypatch):\n        # agent.py scan --foo bar -> mode_words=[\"scan\"], extra=[\"--foo\",\"bar\"]\n        ...\n```\n\n---\n\n",
